
This diagram captures key classes, their attributes, and relationships according to the system requirements:

@startuml
' Sober Taxi System Class Diagram

class Car {
  -carId: String
  -licensePlate: String
  -owner: Owner
  -isSelfDriving: Boolean
  -accidents: List<Accident>
}

class Owner {
  -ownerId: String
  -fullName: String
  -email: String
  -phoneNumber: String
  -registeredCars: List<Car>
}

class Customer {
  -customerId: String
  -fullName: String
  -email: String
  -phoneNumber: String
  -rideShareBookings: List<RideShareBooking>
  -rideHailBookings: List<RideHailBooking>
}

class RideService {
  -serviceId: String
  -pickupTime: DateTime
  -dropoffTime: DateTime
  -pickupLocation: Location
  -dropoffLocation: Location
  -rideDuration: Integer
  -distance: Double
  -fee: Double
}

class RideHailBooking extends RideService {
  -requestType: RequestType (APP or HAND_WAVING)
  -leadCustomer: Customer
  -passengerCount: Integer (1..6)
}

class RideShareBooking extends RideService {
  -negotiatedFee: Double
  -customerList: List<Customer>
  -passengerCount: Integer (1..10)
  -treesPlanted: Boolean
}

class Accident {
  -accidentId: String
  -date: DateTime
  -location: Location
  -damageAmount: Double
}

class Location {
  -latitude: Double
  -longitude: Double
  -address: String
}

enum RequestType {
  APP
  HAND_WAVING
}

' Relationships
Car "1" -- "0..*" Accident : has
Owner "1" -- "0..*" Car : owns
Customer "1" -- "0..*" RideHailBooking : booked
Customer "1" -- "0..*" RideShareBooking : booked
RideHailBooking "1" -- "1" Customer : leadCustomer
RideShareBooking "1" -- "*" Customer : customerList
@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Classes:

- **`Car`**: Represents a vehicle, whether owned by Sober or registered by an individual.
- **`Owner`**: Manages registered car owners who can offer their cars as Sober cabs.
- **`Customer`**: Users of the service who can hail or share rides.
- **`RideService`**: Abstract base class for both ride-hailing and ride-sharing services.
- **`RideHailBooking` & `RideShareBooking`**: Concrete types of ride services with specific properties.
- **`Accident`**: Tracks incidents involving cars.
- **`Location`**: Captures geographical details.
- **`RequestType`**: Enum indicating how a ride was requested (via app or hand-waving).

